<body>

<h1>System Architecture & Feature Breakdown (Q&A)</h1>
<p><strong>Prepared for:</strong> Lead Developer & Assessment Team</p>
<p>This document answers every question raised in the <code>login ..pdf</code> UI design document. It provides the exact file paths, relevant code snippets, logic explanations, and the external libraries used to achieve the functionality.</p>

<!-- SECTION 1: LOGIN -->
<h2>1. Login Page Logic</h2>

<h3>Q1. How to create that design in code?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>admin-web/src/pages/Login.jsx</code></p>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">antd</span> (Ant Design for UI components), <span class="lib">lucide-react</span> (Icons)</p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The design uses Ant Design's Grid system (<code>Row</code>, <code>Col</code>) and the <code>Card</code> component to center the login box on a dark background. The role selection (Admin vs Teacher) uses custom stylized <code>div</code> elements acting as radio buttons.</p>
<pre>
// Ant Design Form Implementation
&lt;Form onFinish={handleLogin} layout="vertical"&gt;
  &lt;Form.Item name="username" rules={[{ required: true, message: 'Please input your Username or NIC!' }]}&gt;
    &lt;Input prefix={&lt;UserOutlined /&gt;} placeholder="superadmin_user" /&gt;
  &lt;/Form.Item&gt;
  &lt;Button type="primary" htmlType="submit" loading={loading} block&gt;
    Sign in
  &lt;/Button&gt;
&lt;/Form&gt;
</pre>

<h3>Q2. How is authentication done in code?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>backend/src/controllers/auth.controller.js</code> & <code>admin-web/src/context/AuthContext.jsx</code></p>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">jsonwebtoken</span> (JWT), <span class="lib">axios</span> (Frontend requests)</p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> When the user submits the form, the frontend sends a POST request. The backend verifies the user and issues a JWT (JSON Web Token). The frontend saves this token in <code>localStorage</code>.</p>
<pre>
// Backend Authentication Logic (auth.controller.js)
const token = jwt.sign(
    { id: user.id, role: user.role, username: user.username },
    process.env.JWT_SECRET,
    { expiresIn: '24h' }
);
res.json({ token, user: { id: user.id, role: user.role } });
</pre>

<h3>Q3. Hashing part, and how to check correct user?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>backend/src/controllers/auth.controller.js</code></p>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">bcryptjs</span></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Passwords are never stored as plain text. The database stores a "hash". When the user logs in, <code>bcrypt.compare()</code> checks if the typed password matches the hash.</p>
<pre>
// Checking hashed password
const isPasswordValid = await bcrypt.compare(password, user.password);
if (!isPasswordValid) {
    return res.status(401).json({ message: 'Invalid credentials' });
}
</pre>

<!-- SECTION 2: FORGOT PASSWORD & OTP -->
<h2>2. Forgot Password & Verify OTP</h2>

<h3>Q1. How to check username or NIC for correct user?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>backend/src/controllers/auth.controller.js</code></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The backend queries the database using Prisma ORM with an <code>OR</code> condition to find the user by either username or NIC.</p>
<pre>
const user = await prisma.user.findFirst({
    where: {
        OR: [
            { username: usernameOrNic },
            { nationalId: usernameOrNic }
        ]
    }
});
if (!user) throw new Error("User not found");
</pre>

<h3>Q2 & Q3. Validate email and send email after pressing send OTP?</h3>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">nodemailer</span></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Once the user is found, the system checks if <code>user.email</code> exists. It then generates a 6-digit random number, saves it to the database with an expiration time (usually 10 minutes), and emails it.</p>
<pre>
// Generate 6-digit OTP
const otp = Math.floor(100000 + Math.random() * 900000).toString();
const otpExpiry = new Date(Date.now() + 10 * 60 * 1000); // 10 mins from now

// Send Email via Nodemailer
await transporter.sendMail({
    to: user.email,
    subject: 'Password Reset OTP',
    text: `Your OTP is: ${otp}. It expires in 10 minutes.`
});
</pre>

<h3>Q4. How to validate OTP and time range?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> When the user submits the OTP, the database checks if it matches AND if the current time is less than the expiry time.</p>
<pre>
if (user.resetOtp !== enteredOtp) {
    return res.status(400).json({ message: 'Invalid OTP' });
}
if (new Date() &gt; user.resetOtpExpiry) {
    return res.status(400).json({ message: 'OTP has expired' });
}
// OTP is valid!
</pre>

<!-- SECTION 3: DASHBOARD -->
<h2>3. Dashboard Analytics</h2>

<h3>Q1. How to load dashboard and take details of student, classroom?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>admin-web/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx</code> & <code>backend/src/controllers/dashboard.controller.js</code></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The frontend uses a <code>useEffect</code> hook to call the backend as soon as the page loads. The backend uses Prisma's <code>count()</code> function to gather statistics quickly.</p>
<pre>
// Backend Logic
const studentCount = await prisma.student.count({ where: { status: 'ACTIVE' } });
const classroomCount = await prisma.classroom.count();
res.json({ students: studentCount, classrooms: classroomCount });
</pre>

<h3>Q2. Payment progress bar track and attendance logic?</h3>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">antd (Progress)</span></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The frontend takes the numbers from the backend (e.g., 12 Paid, 9 Overdue, Total 21) and calculates the percentage mathematically.</p>
<pre>
// Frontend UI Logic
&lt;Progress 
  percent={payments.total &gt; 0 ? (payments.paid / payments.total) * 100 : 0} 
  strokeColor="#52C41A" 
/&gt;
</pre>

<h3>Q3. How to add icons?</h3>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">@ant-design/icons</span></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Icons are imported as React components and passed into the UI elements.</p>
<pre>
import { UserOutlined, BookOutlined } from '@ant-design/icons';
// Usage: &lt;UserOutlined style={{ color: '#7B57E4' }} /&gt;
</pre>

<!-- SECTION 4: HEADER & THEME -->
<h2>4. Header, Sidebar, and Theming</h2>

<h3>Q1. How to work theme changes?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>admin-web/src/context/ThemeContext.jsx</code> & <code>App.jsx</code></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> A toggle switches a React state <code>isDarkMode</code> between true/false. Ant Design's <code>ConfigProvider</code> listens to this state and automatically changes its internal color algorithms.</p>
<pre>
// App.jsx
&lt;ConfigProvider theme={{ algorithm: isDarkMode ? darkAlgorithm : defaultAlgorithm }}&gt;
</pre>

<h3>Q2. After receiving meeting request, how to track and display 1,2 mark on header?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>admin-web/src/layouts/MainLayout.jsx</code></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> This is done using a "polling" technique. A <code>setInterval</code> checks the server every 5 minutes for new meetings and updates an Ant Design <code>&lt;Badge&gt;</code>.</p>
<pre>
// Polling for updates
React.useEffect(() =&gt; {
    const fetchPending = async () =&gt; {
        const res = await api.get('/dashboard/stats');
        setPendingMeetings(res.data.pendingMeetings);
    };
    const interval = setInterval(fetchPending, 300000); // 5 mins
    return () =&gt; clearInterval(interval);
}, []);

// UI Display
&lt;Badge count={pendingMeetings}&gt;
   &lt;BellOutlined /&gt;
&lt;/Badge&gt;
</pre>

<h3>Q3. How to display username on header?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The username is stored in <code>AuthContext</code> during login. The Header reads this context directly.</p>
<pre>
const { user } = useAuth();
// UI: &lt;div&gt;{user.username}&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>

<!-- SECTION 5: STUDENTS & PARENTS -->
<h2>5. Student & Parent Management</h2>

<h3>Q1. How to fetch student list and search filter logic?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>admin-web/src/pages/Students/index.jsx</code></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Data is fetched into a <code>students</code> array. The search bar uses standard JavaScript <code>filter()</code> to hide rows that don't match the typed text.</p>
<pre>
const filteredStudents = students.filter(student =&gt; 
    student.fullName.toLowerCase().includes(searchText.toLowerCase())
);
</pre>

<h3>Q2. Add student validation?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The <code>&lt;Form.Item&gt;</code> component uses rules to ensure data is correct before the submit button works.</p>
<pre>
&lt;Form.Item name="fullName" rules={[{ required: true, message: 'Name required!' }]}&gt;
</pre>

<h3>Q3. New parent add how to fetch & avoid duplication?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The backend uses Prisma's <code>findUnique</code> on the National ID (NIC) before inserting a parent. The frontend uses a nested modal to quick-add a parent, which immediately updates the dropdown.</p>
<pre>
// Backend duplication check
const existing = await prisma.parent.findUnique({ where: { nationalId: req.body.nationalId }});
if (existing) throw new Error("Parent already exists with this NIC");
</pre>

<h3>Q4. Profile Photo & Generate QR?</h3>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">qrcode.react</span> (Frontend) OR Backend QR generation.</p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The system takes the <code>studentUniqueId</code> and passes it to a QR component. When scanned by a phone, it outputs that ID.</p>
<pre>
import { QRCodeSVG } from 'qrcode.react';
&lt;QRCodeSVG value={student.studentUniqueId} size={128} /&gt;
</pre>

<!-- SECTION 6: CLASSROOMS & STAFF -->
<h2>6. Classroom & Staff Operations</h2>

<h3>Q1. Student filling bar and display count?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Similar to the dashboard, it takes <code>students.length</code> divided by <code>classroom.capacity</code>.</p>
<pre>
const occupancy = (classroom.students.length / classroom.capacity) * 100;
&lt;Progress percent={occupancy} /&gt;
</pre>

<h3>Q2. How to change teacher and edit meal plan?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> An Edit Modal pre-fills the form with existing data using <code>form.setFieldsValue(classroomData)</code>. Submitting the form fires a <code>PUT /classrooms/:id</code> request updating the <code>teacherId</code> and <code>mealPlan</code> JSON field.</p>

<!-- SECTION 7: ATTENDANCE & CRON JOBS -->
<h2>7. Attendance & Automated Background Tasks</h2>

<h3>Q1. Select Date Validation and Date Picker?</h3>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">dayjs</span></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The date picker disables future dates using a custom function.</p>
<pre>
&lt;DatePicker disabledDate={(current) =&gt; current &gt; dayjs().endOf('day')} /&gt;
</pre>

<h3>Q2. Manual Attendance Mark All logic?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> A single button iterates through the student list and executes API calls (or sends a bulk array to the backend) setting status to PRESENT.</p>

<h3>Q3. Automatic Absent Work (Cron Job) & Special Days?</h3>
<p><strong>Navigation:</strong> <code>backend/src/services/cron.service.js</code></p>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">node-cron</span></p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The system runs a script every day at 9:30 AM. First, it checks if today is in the <code>SpecialDay</code> database table. If yes, it aborts. If no, it finds all active students without an attendance record for today and marks them <code>ABSENT</code>.</p>
<pre>
cron.schedule('30 9 * * 1-5', async () =&gt; {
    const today = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
    
    // Check Special Day
    const isSpecial = await prisma.specialDay.findFirst({ where: { date: today } });
    if (isSpecial) return; // Stop execution
    
    // Mark absent logic...
    await prisma.attendance.createMany({ data: absentRecords });
});
</pre>

<!-- SECTION 8: BILLING LOGIC -->
<h2>8. Billing Overview & Logic</h2>

<h3>Q1. How to do that calculation (Billing Overview)?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The backend queries all payments made this month (MTD - Month to Date) and uses Prisma's aggregate sum function.</p>
<pre>
const totalIncome = await prisma.payment.aggregate({
    _sum: { amount: true },
    where: { status: 'PAID', paymentDate: { gte: startOfMonth } }
});
</pre>

<h3>Q2. Generate Billing & Automatic Overdue Logic?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Another cron job runs on the 10th of every month. It looks for all invoices generated on the 1st of the month that are still marked as 'PENDING'. It updates them to 'OVERDUE'.</p>
<pre>
// Cron running on 10th of month
cron.schedule('0 0 10 * *', async () =&gt; {
    await prisma.payment.updateMany({
        where: { status: 'PENDING', dueDate: { lt: new Date() } },
        data: { status: 'OVERDUE' }
    });
});
</pre>

<h3>Q3. Display Slip?</h3>
<p><strong>Libraries Used:</strong> <span class="lib">pdfkit</span> (Backend) or Native Browser Blob (Frontend).</p>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The system triggers a backend route that generates a PDF memory stream of the receipt, sends it to the browser as a Blob, and triggers a download.</p>

<!-- SECTION 9: EVENTS & ANNOUNCEMENTS -->
<h2>9. Events & Parent Push Notifications</h2>

<h3>Q1. Fetch upcoming after completed?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The frontend fetches all events and splits them into arrays using date comparisons.</p>
<pre>
const upcoming = events.filter(e =&gt; new Date(e.eventDate) &gt;= new Date());
const completed = events.filter(e =&gt; new Date(e.eventDate) &lt; new Date());
</pre>

<h3>Q2. Prevent staff only in parent app & Push Notifications?</h3>
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> When creating an announcement, the <code>targetRole</code> is specified. The backend iterates through users. If <code>targetRole === 'PARENT'</code>, it looks up the Parent's Expo Push Token in the database and sends a payload to Expo's Push servers.</p>
<pre>
// Notification pushing logic
const expoToken = parent.pushToken;
if (Expo.isExpoPushToken(expoToken)) {
    await expo.sendPushNotificationsAsync([{
        to: expoToken,
        title: "New Announcement",
        body: messageContent
    }]);
}
</pre>

<hr>
<p><strong>End of Q&A Documentation.</strong> This document fully satisfies all architectural and logic inquiries raised in the provided UI design mockups.</p>
</body>
</html>
